MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Server (24/24 tests):
- Board extends Community (not a separate entity): item{id,url,
  canonicalKey,title,image,siteName,addedBy,comments[],votes,decided},
  keyed by canonicalKey to prevent duplicate listings from re-adds with
  different tracking params
- board_add_item / board_remove_item (admin or original adder) /
  board_comment / board_vote (toggle) / board_decide (admin-only,
  concludes the group's decision)
- membership-gated like everything else in a community: non-members
  receive nothing, verified by test
- board state persists with the community (deliberately NOT
  zero-retention like chat — boards are meant to outlive a session,
  that's the point)

Extension — the anchoring engine (the actual moat, not flashy):
- lib/anchor.ts: tiered canonical-key extraction — site-aware
  extractors for Airbnb/Amazon/Zillow/Booking.com/Etsy pull the stable
  listing ID straight from the URL path (survives re-visits, tracking
  param changes, personalized layouts), falling back to <link
  rel=canonical>, falling back to origin+path with UTM/ref/fbclid/gclid
  stripped
- content script (previously unused WXT scaffold) now serves
  read-only page anchors on request — no UI injected into visited
  pages, passive by design
- 'Add current tab to board' pulls the anchor via the content script,
  gracefully falls back to tab.url/title on restricted pages
  (chrome://, etc.)

UI: BoardView inside each community — item cards (image/title/site),
vote (toggle, visible count), expandable comment thread, admin-only
decide/reopen with a visible 'Decided' banner, remove restricted to
admin or adder. Chat/Board segmented control added to community
ChatView; board tab count badge.
